## Car Inventory App

-A simple full-stack car inventory application built with React (frontend) and Node.js + Express
(backend).

-It allows users to add, edit, view, and delete cars using a clean and responsive interface.
-All data is saved in a local cars.json file for simplicity.

## Project Structure

my_cars_api/
-cars.json # Local file-based "database"
-server.js # Express backend API
-package.json # Backend dependencies
-client/ # React frontend
-src/
-App.js
-index.js
-index.css
...
-package.json # Frontend dependencies

## Features

- Add new cars with make, model, and year
- Edit car details
- Delete a car
- View all cars in a list
- Simple file-based storage (cars.json)
- Responsive Bootstrap UI

## Installation

1. Clone the repo
   -git clone https://github.com/your-username/car-inventory-app.git
   -cd car-inventory-app
2. Install backend dependencies
   -npm install
3. Start the backend server
   -npm start
   > The server will run on http://localhost:3001
4. Start the frontend (in a new terminal tab)
   -cd client
   -npm install
   -npm start
   > The frontend will run on http://localhost:3000

## API Endpoints

Method | Endpoint | Description
GET | /cars | Get all cars
POST | /cars | Add a new car
PUT | /cars/:id | Update a car
DELETE | /cars/:id | Delete a car

## Tech Stack

- Frontend: React, Bootstrap
- Backend: Node.js, Express
- Storage: JSON file (cars.json)

## Testing

Basic component and functionality tests are included using React Testing Library. Run tests with:
npm test (from the client directory)

